Technology Brief -- Apple Computer Inc.:
   Firm Sets Windows Version
   Of Its QuickTime Software
Quicktime is an extension to the basic software used in
Apple's Macintosh computers. The extension, which enables
software applications to handle sound and video along with
traditional text and graphics, is the technical centerpiece
of Apple's move into what it calls "multimedia" computing.
   Chairman and Chief Executive Officer John Sculley, in an
address at a Macintosh trade show, said making QuickTime
available across computer platforms would encourage creators
of applications to take advantage of its features.